descript.abstract: Cadastral data for the City of Somverille, Massachusetts compiled from city GIS data and assessing data.

idinfo.accconst: This digital parcel data layer is considered to be in the public domain and will become accessible for download and display from the MassGIS website: http://www.mass.gov/mgis
idinfo.useconst: This data may be appropriate for planning purposes. It should not be utilized where legal and surveyed property boundaries are required.
idinfo.native: This parcel data is submitted to MassGIS in a file geodatabase. It will be incorporated into the MassGIS SDE database, and may be converted into other GIS data types for future distribution.

dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

horizpa.horizpar: Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

srcinfo.srccontr: Parcel boundaries were originally digitized in 1999 from the 117 existing hard copy Assessor's Tax Maps. Parcel boundaries and Identifiers are maintained by CDM Smith and the City of Somerville assessing department and are updated every few years.

procstep.procdesc: Data was processed to meet MassGIS Level III formatting standards including reviewing the city boundary and adding standard fields and definitions. Gaps representing street ROWs were filled in as per the Level III requirements.

overview.dsoverv: Parcel boundaries were originally digitized from the Assessor's 117 80-scale tax maps. Parcel boundaries and Identifiers are maintained by CDM Smith and the City of Somerville assessing department and are updated every few years. To meet MassGIS Level III parcel standards, parcel boundaries were reveiwed against the ROWs and other features shown on the MassGIS 2008/2009 orthophotos.

distinfo.resdesc: M274TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Somerville that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M274Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M274OthLeg and M274Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
